      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_RateFactorUpdate",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update a record in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "RateFactor",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "input",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " schema. It modifies specific fields of a record identified by a unique "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ID",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": ". The procedure updates fields such as fiscal year, name, description, active status, and records the user who performed the update along with the current timestamp."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "UPDATE",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " statement that modifies a record based on a primary key. There are no complex joins, subqueries, or conditional logic, making it easy to understand and maintain."
        }
      ]
    },
